Leicester City Council (the Owner) invites Tenders for the provision of the development of the new industrial units at the Ian Marlow Centre site. A summary of what the tenderer is being requested to deliver is as follows:- 

Appoint and oversee a design team to progress the design development and detailed design for the works including any survey work deemed required; 

Undertake demolition works prior to planning approval which will be paid by the Owner; 

Submit the planning application 

Works undertaken to be paid in line with stage payments set out in the Delivery Agreement; 

Obtain all necessary consents under the Development Agreement; 

Report on progress to the Owner and their Consultants on a monthly basis (via Teams); 

Develop an overall programme for the scheme identifying a period of two weeks for key Owner sign off periods at a time (planning submission, out to tender, tender approval); 

Appoint a main contractor to construct the scheme and manage/ oversee the project whilst on site; 

Allow for any relevant Owner training required; 

12 month mechanical and electrical maintenance contract for the site; 

12 month landscaping maintenance for the site; 

 

Please refer to other tender documentation for further information. Tender documentation available at https://procontract.due-north.com/

The Authority has secured funding for the following project:
      o Pitched and Flat Roofing Replacement Works at Cold Harbour CofE Primary School 
      
      The Project Objectives are to ensure that: 
      
      o The project is to ensure minimal disruption of the school's operations during works and be collaborative with the school;
      o The flat roof covering systems are to meet the fire classification of BS EN 13501-5 Broof(T4);
      o The pitched roof covering systems are to meet the British Standard for Slating and Tiling (BS 5534);
      o Works are to enhance the School Building by upgrading poor condition elements;
      o Works are to improve the energy efficiency of the School Building in accordance with Building Regulations Part L;
      o Rainwater goods are safe and easy to clean and maintain;
      o Roof coverings installed are to be those specified or equal and approved;
      o Works are carried out in compliance with CDM Regulations 2015, to ensure the health and safety of contractors, workers and end users of the property; and
      o Works are completed on time, within budget and to a high quality in order to obtain the associated guarantees.
